<span id="freeTextContainer17634678579208556915">I should start by saying that I won this book in a giveaway here on Goodreads. Honestly, I don&apos;t know what I was expecting when I first started because the description is slightly vague, but I ended up spending most of the day finishing it in one sitting because I didn&apos;t want to put it down. If you love darker books like me, then The Sorrow&apos;s Garden is perfect for you. The writing was easy to follow and I found myself quickly attached to, yet slightly horrified of, the main character. It&apos;s hard </span>
